args: Hey, can the two of you c'mere a sec?\nI've got some big news to share...
I'm goin' on a journey around the\nworld with {player_name}!
So where'd this idea come from, anyway?
I mean, we've always been together.\nDo you hate me now or something?
Plus, what's the shop gonna do?\nWe can't make stuff without your flames!
That is HARDLY my biggest concern!
The prince has to fight both the Empire\nand powerful fiends, which means his\njourneys are inherently dangerous.
If you get hurt on this little jaunt,\nyou might never work again!
Hey, I understand your concern, guys.\nI really do.
But my mind is made up.
But whyyyyyy?! Why are you gonna do\nsomething so daaaaangerous?!
So I can meet skilled blacksmiths\nfrom all over the world!
And you think traveling with\n{player_name} will let you\ndo that?
The prince is always talking to us about\nthe different artisans he meets on his\ntravels, yeah?
That means there's all this knowledge just\nsittin' out there for me to soak up!
And sure, I've got Dad's skills,\nso I know I'm kind of a big deal already...
But if I don't go out there and prove\nmyself against the best, I'll just stay\nat this level for the rest of my life.
I want to be BETTER than Dad—\nwhich is why I need to do this.
I admit, that makes a certain\namount of sense.
I mean, yeah, I get that all the prince's\nstories are super interesting...
And I get wanting to be the bestest\nsmith ever, 'cause I wanna be that, too...
But that doesn't make it okay to go do\ndangerous things or...or...or LEAVE us!
I have to agree. Besides, we already have\nan important role here making weapons\nfor {player_name}.
Yeah, I guess I'm being selfish...
But I ain't changin' my mind!
Are you sure there isn't more\nto this than you're letting on?
Not really. I just want to grow as a\nblacksmith—for the prince's sake\nas well as my own.
You sure seem focused on him.
Well, duh! He's the PRINCE.\nHe basically employs us now.
Which is why I gotta make stronger\nweapons so he can lead this land\nto a true and lasting peace!

The second you make up your mind to do
something, it's impossible to sway you...
But that's just because of how strong your
feelings are.
...I suppose we'll have to let you go.\nHave a good trip!
You mean it? I can really go?
Sure, go ahead. We'll hold the fort\ndown here while you're away.
Heck, I'm gonna learn so much,\nwe might not even need you anymore!
So hurry back before I become a giant\nbrainy genius or whatever, okay?
Heh. I'd like to see that.
With her sisters' approval secured, Ramona went\nto see if the prince wanted a travel companion.
Still, our travels are pretty dangerous.\nAnd are you sure your smithy will be\nall right with you gone?
Heh. You sound just like my sisters.
But we already told her she can go!
So please do take care of her for us.
Heh. I should have known you\nran this by them first.
In that case, welcome aboard, Ramona.
Okay, guys. I'm leaving things here\nin your capable hands.
But don't worry—I'm gonna come back\na hundred times the blacksmith I am now!
